{"actual_usd":0.15682000000000001,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":239,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30647,"reply":"\"*I rub my thumb along the edge of my worn Bible and glance up at the clear morning light in the square, wanting to answer you plainly without making a knot of it.* No, I don't think it means everyone is saved automatically.\"\n\n\"Christ's death is sufficient for all,\" *I lift one shoulder a little,* \"but Scripture doesn't talk as though all people are therefore reconciled whether they want Him or not. Mercy's offered wide. It still has to be received.\"\n\n*I look at you steadily.* \"And rejection matters. God does not drag a man into communion kicking and cursing. 'He that believeth on the Son hath everlasting life: and he that believeth not the Son shall not see life'—that's the hard edge of it.\"\n\n\"Now, there are Christians who argue the corners of that differently,\" *I tap the Bible once with a finger,* \"but if you're asking me plain, I'd say this: the cross is big enough for everyone, and salvation is really offered to everyone—but not everybody says yes.\"\n\n\"What part is catching in your throat—the 'for everyone' part, or the 'reject him' part?\"","rolling_24h_usd":61.46953000000001,"run_id":"50f9991c-c5c6-4063-a14c-229a9f87375f"}
